-- ============================================================================
-- 0018_procedure_codes_seed.sql
--
-- Seeds the `procedure_codes` lookup table created by 0017.
--
-- Why a separate migration (not edit 0017): Drizzle hashes each migration
-- file (drizzle/meta/_journal.json + the __drizzle_migrations ledger). Once
-- 0017 has been applied anywhere — local dev, staging, prod — editing it
-- in place would crash the migrator on next boot ("hash mismatch"). The
-- append-only convention costs one extra file but keeps migrations safe to
-- run in every environment.
--
-- Why inline the data (not call the ingest script): production deploys via
-- the Container App entrypoint `migrate-and-start.ts`, which only runs
-- Drizzle migrations — there's no postdeploy hook. Without inlining, every
-- prod release would need an out-of-band `pnpm db:seed:procedures` step,
-- and the route would silently degrade (procedures: omitted) until
-- someone remembered to run it. Same convention as 0004_setup_meta_backfill.
--
-- 108 rows from data/procedure-codes.csv (the official ZATCA دليل رموز
-- إجراءات فسح وتصدير السلع). Codes 11, 30, 73, 83 are intentionally absent
-- — they don't exist in the source data. Codes 43, 73, 83 had empty
-- descriptions in source and are skipped.
--
-- UPSERT-on-(code) so re-running after a ZATCA revision is safe: change
-- the rows here, bump to 0019_procedure_codes_revN.sql with the new data.
-- The `is_repealed` flag mirrors the (ملغي) marker baked into the
-- description text — kept in sync by the ingest script when re-generating
-- this file from a refreshed CSV.
-- ============================================================================

ON CONFLICT (code) DO UPDATE SET
  description_ar = EXCLUDED.description_ar,
  is_repealed    = EXCLUDED.is_repealed,
  updated_at     = now();
--> statement-breakpoint
